OL,7,FA romantic-mystery debut novel based
OL,8,Fin sun-soaked southern France has won
OL,9,Fthe 2025 Waterstones Book of the Year.
OL,11,FSet across a Provencal summer in 1920,
OL,12,FLucy Steeds' The Artist follows an
OL,13,Fenigmatic painter, his niece and a
OL,14,FBritish journalist who is keen on
OL,15,Fwriting a piece about him, before
OL,16,Ftensions begin to build between them
OL,17,Fall.
