OL,7,FBea Carvalho, Waterstones' head of
OL,8,Fbooks said: "The Artist is a
OL,9,Fgorgeously escapist novel which
OL,10,Fseamlessly transports the reader to
OL,11,Fthe sticky heat of sun-soaked 1920s'
OL,12,Fsouthern France, weaving mystery with
OL,13,Fromance while delving into the complex
OL,14,Fnature of artistry.
OL,16,F"Atmospheric, elegant and sensory, it
OL,17,Fis a novel to be fully swept away by.
